Here the main idea is to add LFO Sines to get a complex curve and to use this curve for the Filter CutOff value of a Saw.
I use also the folded version of this Curve to add synced variations to the initial curve.

I Also add a high Sine 'flute' in the mix of the unfolded version of the sound.

I did then add a 'simple' techno drum machine using an FM modulating FM (sine-sine) Synth for the shaker. Some of the drum goes into the reverb process, some of it gets a little delay and goes dry in the mix.

I did a rich use of Sine FLO for modulating some Attacks, Release and other factors. It brings more live to the thing.

I've made a use of Filter subtraction to equalize the sound at the end. This is very useful. I have to use it more often.

Two banks for BD&HH sequencer and Two for the Shaker (make your own).
